DAY 05:
1.ID 
  *The id attribute gives an element a unique identifier within the page.
  *Only one element on a page should use a particular id.
  *IDs are useful when you need to target one specific element for styling or scripting.

2.CLASSES
  *The class attribute lets you assign a name that can be shared by multiple elements.
  *Classes are great for grouping elements that should share styles or behavior.

3.DIV
  *The id attribute gives an element a unique identifier within the page.
  *Only one element on a page should use a particular id.
  *IDs are useful when you need to target one specific element for styling or scripting.


EXAMPLE:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <style>
    #header {
      font-size: 36px;
      text-align: center;
      color: green;
    }
    .box {
      border: 2px solid black;
      padding: 10px;
      margin: 10px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1 id="header">My Website</h1>

  <div class="box">Box 1</div>
  <div class="box">Box 2</div>

</body>
</html>


